  "text": "Despite the broad scope of applications ranging from biology (e.g. biological cells [CITATION_1] or vesicles [CITATION_2] in a viscous shear flow) to large scale structures (e.g. parachute aerodynamics [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and flutter of air-plane wings [CITATION_5] ), modelling of fluid-solid interaction has been still in development due to its multi-physics nature over ranges of time-and length-scales. Numerical simulation is suitable for handling a wider range of fluid-structure properties that are inaccessible by experiments simultaneously and non-invasively.",
